<font color="#FF0000">COME HOME</font><br>
<tt>Wed Apr 30 20:43:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Del, I am going to post this here rather than on e-mail because I think that it is important that all read this.  <br>
I wish that there was a thing that I could give you that could bring you back.  All that I see you post is compared to experiences in Nam.  There must be a way for you to come home.  Can you not see that?  All the things that we discuss on and off line relates to Nam.  Can't live like that.  It almost put me up &quot;in a tower&quot;.  The hardest thing for me to do was put it into the place that it needs to be; The Past. Granted it took six years of talking, crying and writing letters.  But one day I knew I was home.  I wish you could come home, too.<br>
Vietnam still causes my ears to point but I can talk about it in the respect that it happened and yes, it screwed my head up but bro, come home.<br>
If not for you; try for those who care and love you.<br>
I appreciate that you might blow me up but the last couple of posts have generated a lot of concern.
<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


